slot.description: Specifies the Slot ID of a service board.

engine.description: The value is NA when the service is based on slot or card. This parameter can only be configured on a centralized-boards.

card.description: The value is NA when the service is based on slot or engine. This parameter takes effect only on a VSUF-80 or VSUF-160 or VSUI-160-E.

pool-address-usage.description: Address usage of an IP address pool. If a section is locked, an attempt to apply for public IP addresses may fail even if address usage is not 100%.

pool-port-usage.description: Users' actual port usage. The value is the number of user actually used ports/Total number of ports (Reserved ports are not counted for the actually used ports and total ports).

pcp-allcated-port-usage.description: Usage of the reserved PCP ports allocated by the RADIUS service. The value is the number of PCP ports allocated by the RADIUS service/Total number of reserved ports.

pcp-reserved-port-usage.description: Users' actual usage of reserved PCP ports. The value is the number of user actually used PCP ports/Total number of reserved ports (Well-known ports are not counted for the actually used PCP ports and reserved ports).
